body:
This commit cleans up the codebase by removing lingering Python 2 specific constructs.

**Update:** After #5824 did most of the work, the changes remaining in this PR are very small.

comment_data.body:
The two different int types are gone as well.
```suggestion
               builtin_sequence_types=object)
```

comment_data.body:
It was even only one occurrence (see 9fff260), here's the full diff:

```diff
diff --git a/Cython/Compiler/TreePath.py b/Cython/Compiler/TreePath.py
index b1371c249a5..007581890d9 100644
--- a/Cython/Compiler/TreePath.py
+++ b/Cython/Compiler/TreePath.py
@@ -11,8 +11,6 @@
 import operator
 import sys
 
-_unicode = str
-
 path_tokenizer = re.compile(
     r"("
     r"'[^']*'|\"[^\"]*\"|"
@@ -165,7 +163,7 @@ def select(result):
                     continue
                 if attr_value == value:
                     yield attr_value
-                elif (isinstance(attr_value, bytes) and isinstance(value, _unicode) and
+                elif (isinstance(attr_value, bytes) and isinstance(value, str) and
                         attr_value == value.encode()):
                     # allow a bytes-to-string comparison too
                     yield attr_value
```

commit.message:
Refactor UnicodeLiteralBuilder for Python 3 compatibility

String Handling: In Python 3, all strings are unicode by default. The explicit distinction between unicode and byte strings (as was necessary in Python 2) is no longer required. This simplification allows us to remove the conditional check for byte strings in the append method.
